This paper is about personalized expertise search on LinkedIn, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques such as ranking and recommendation. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses collaborative filtering, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions handling biases in search logs, which is related to statistical learning (cs.SD) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper mentions using natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract features, which falls under the sub-category of computation and language (cs.CL).
